Method Detail

autoLb

public boolean autoLb()
Returns whether or not this forwarded performs automatic load balancing. When true, this forwarder selects a new indexer every autoLBFrequency seconds, or immediately when an open connection to an indexer is lost.

Returns:
Whether or not this forwarder performs automatic load balancing.

blockOnQueueFull

public boolean blockOnQueueFull()
Returns whether or not this forwarder will block. If set to false, events will get thrown away if no indexers in the group are reachable.

Returns:
Whether or not this forwarder will block.

Returns:
this forwards auto load balancing frequency.

getDefaultGroup

public java.lang.String getDefaultGroup()
Returns this forwarder's default group as a comma separated list, or null if not specified. After Splunk 4.2, this attribute is no longer required.

Returns:
this forwarder's default group list.

getDropEventsOnQueueFull

public int getDropEventsOnQueueFull()
Returns the number of second this forwarder's waits before throwing out events if the output queue is full. A setting of 0 or -1 causes this forwarder to block.

Returns:
this forwards wait time, in seconds, before events are dropped under queue full conditions.
